The paper discusses the Dendritic Cell Algorithm (DCA) and its application to anomaly detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also compares the DCA to a Self-Organizing Map (SOM), which is a type of artificial neural network, indicating a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The DCA is a biologically inspired algorithm, which suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
